body:
I know what I would choose but I thought I would mention it here. What's the style guide for if else if else formatting.

``` javascript
if (condition) {
  //stuff
} else {
  //stuff
}
```

vs

``` javascript
if (condition) {
  //stuff
}
else {
  //stuff
}
```

I think the choice is obvious but, "I've heard it both ways".
